This paper discusses the design of an anonymity system that is resistant to intersection attacks, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) literature. The system involves dynamically grouping users, which suggests a potential connection to distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between anonymity and communication responsiveness, which could be relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a specific design for the anonymity system, which could be considered a contribution to cryptography (cs.CY).
